title: Broken Cracked Sidewalk
author: ashlyn
text: broken cracked sidewalk.  you still stand on this lovely earth so free.  your cracks fill with water when it rains.  your edges are chipped and fall off from time to time.  you carry my weight as i walk across your surface.  broken cracked sidewalk.   broken cracked sidewalk.  they want to tear you up.  they don't want to fix you.  they don't care about you.  they don't want to help you.  broken cracked sidewalk.   broken cracked sidewalk.  you are the path to these lovely homes on this street.  they look so new and you look so old.  you are the path to many peoples' hearts.  they are the hearts that appreciate your acquaintance.  broken cracked sidewalk.   broken cracked sidewalk.  i think about you everyday.  i think about the strength you have.  i think about the struggles you went through.  i share your pains.  broken cracked sidewalk.   broken cracked sidewalk.  i'll miss your cracks you hold.  i'll miss walking on you through the rain.  i'll miss your chipped edges that break.  i'll miss the strength you carry.  broken cracked sidewalk.   broken cracked sidewalk.  i want to stay with the broken cracked sidewalk.  i want to follow the broken cracked sidewalk.  i want to forever walk on the broken cracked sidewalk.  i will go with the broken cracked sidewalk.  broken cracked sidewalk.

text: the thunder boomed loud and mad,  the rain continued crying,  tears of sad,   the lightning struck,  silent not a sound,  just a tearful pitter-patter upon the the ground,   the thunder decided he shall rule the sky,  so he boomed to the lightning,  sianara, goodbye,   the lightning sent a strike straight towards the ground,  the thunder laughed,  and said, ''you must be weak if you can't make a sound''  the lightning got fierce,  lit up the sky,  replied to the thunder, ''i won't say goodbye''  their battle raged a boom,  a flash,  below the ground covered with ash,   the rain's tears continued rolling down,  over the earth,  over the ground,   the thunder sent a frightening boom,  the lightning a last firey zoom,   the thunder crashed,  the lightning fell,  the thunder opened his mouth to boom his victory bell,   but when the thunder opened it was dry,  not even allowing the thunder to sigh,   the rain stoped crying turned and stared,  and watched the thunder decide to care,   the thunder realized he destroyed his other half,  realized he couldn't walk away from this and laugh,   a rainbow appeared,  shining in the sky,  and let out a beautiful peaceful sigh,   told the thunder to leave and go,  bring the friend you thought a foe,  next time the rain needs to cry,  come to her aide but remember thunder and lightning like night and day,  can share the sky. . . . . .

'' ''you ain't the only person i got to see today so you better go on and say the words that you would like to say'', said the stork.  ''but what if i have nothing to say'' asked the boy.  ''well then i must be going now, '' the stork replied.  ''wait'',  the boy said.  ''thank you very much for my new little sister''said the boy well the stork went on and the little boy was so happy.

title: Oh, the Possibilities
author: brooke
text: oh,  the possibilities of holidays to come.  of shining suns,   and falling snow.  jack-o-lanterns! waving banners!  candy in my bag,  costumes to design,  smiles to shine,  oh,  the possibilities.   yes,  the possibilities,  my birthday's in a week.  i wish for lots of presents.  oh,  the possibilities.  a submarine? crystal set?  awh,  it can't be bedtime yet?! i'll have to make this story short,   for i have dreams to dream.  oh,  the possibilities.

title: The Bar
author: brooke
text: i wait for my turn.  the bar grins at me.  it seems to be saying ''bring it on. '' not this time,  i think.  i'm not afraid of you.  i jump off the block and grasp the bar.  it seems to squirm under my hands as if to shake me off.  no! i won't fall!  i pull myself up to a front support.  when i cast,  i whirl around the bar at mock 5.  almost done,  i think.  i cast once more for my dismount.  in a whirl of chalk my feet hit the mat.  ''ha!'' i say out loud.  the bar seems disappointed.  i have conquered all!
